#
# labwc parses this file itself — it is NOT sourced as a shell script the
# way Openbox does (see labwc-config(5)). Plain KEY=value only, no export,
# no quotes; either one ends up in the literal, un-parsed environment value.
#
# qt6ct, not qt5ct: every Qt app installed here (falkon, pavucontrol-qt,
# pcmanfm-qt) links against Qt6, which can't load the Qt5-only qt5ct
# platform-theme plugin at all.
#

# To set your language for displaying messages and time/date formats, use the following:
#LANG=en_CA.UTF8

# To set your keyboard layout, you need to modify your X config:
# http://www.google.com/search?q=how+to+set+keyboard+layout+xorg
QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct
